    • Constructor Detail

      • LSIClass

        public LSIClass(java.lang.String classToken,
        java.lang.String superClassToken,
        int lsiClassNrOffset,
        int maximumSubclasses,
        java.lang.String className,
        java.lang.String[] synonymNames,
        java.lang.String iconImage,
        int dorendaFlags,
        java.lang.String OSMtags,
        java.lang.String[] properties,
        java.lang.String geomTypes,
        java.lang.String closedLineType)
        Parameters:
        classToken - token for this class
        superClassToken - name of the upper class or "" (not null) for top-level classes
        lsiClassNrOffset - either the first digit lsiClass number (if top-level) or the lower digits, added to the upper class number. If 0, the system defines a number, otherwise 1...maximumSubclasses-1
        maximumSubclasses - typicall 10, but also 100, 1000 possible, 0 means: this class must be a class without any subclasses
        className - a user readable name
        synonymNames - a list of user readable synonym names - these are the searchable strings by the symbole search services. [0] array means NOT searable. null object means, the class name is used
        iconImage - the name of the icon image without path and .png
        dorendaFlags - flags to control map rendering
        OSMtags - sequence of key==value, key!=value, separated by ",", right-hand-side "*" allowed, also key=={value1, value2} or key!={value1, value2}. Komma-separated expressions (considered as AND) can be combinded by || (considered as OR)
        properties - Array of properies, each of it TYPE:osmkey, TYPE: may be omitted, then STRING: is assumed, may be null if no properties during constroction
        geomTypes - string of "P" (point), "L" (line),"A" (area), and "R" (relation) e.g "PLA", "L". "*" is equal to "PLA"
        closedLineType - "R": a closed line is considered as ring, "A" a closed line is considered as area

      • getPropertyDescription

        public static java.lang.String[] getPropertyDescription(int nr)
        Get a property type description. It contains four elements.
        • [0]: the type token
        • [1]: an information text
        • [2]: *: non list value (e.g. integer numbers, L: a list of possible values
        • [3]: examples (non list value) or complete list of possible values
